      "kind": "content",
      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "overview",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Overview",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "The "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "NCWidgetListViewController"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " class provides a list view for displaying content in a Today widget. A list view controller works together with its delegate to display content and support user interaction with the list. To learn about the list view controller delegate methods, see "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/notificationcenter/ncwidgetlistviewdelegate"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "You store the contents of a widget as an array of objects in the list view controller’s "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/notificationcenter/ncwidgetlistviewcontroller/1476057-contents"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " property. To display the objects, you use a "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/notificationcenter/ncwidgetlistviewcontroller/1476044-delegate"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " object, which provides a custom view controller for each object in "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "contents"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": ". A list view controller also provides properties that make it easy to specify aspects of the list’s appearance and behavior, such as the number of rows to display, the presence of divider lines, and the ability to edit the list."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
